{"parse":{"title":"Testerian catechisms","pageid":48796555,"revid":777997845,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-style ambox-Orphan\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"display: none\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Wiki_letter_w.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Wiki letter w.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/40px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/60px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/80px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"44\" data-file-height=\"44\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>is an <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Orphan\" title=\"Wikipedia:Orphan\">orphan</a>, as no other articles <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Whatlinkshere&amp;target=Testerian_catechisms&amp;namespace=0\">link to it</a></b>. Please <a href=\"/wiki/Help:Link\" title=\"Help:Link\">introduce links</a> to this page from <span class=\"plainlinks\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special%3ASearch&amp;redirs=1&amp;search=Testerian+catechisms&amp;fulltext=Search&amp;ns0=1&amp;title=Special%3ASearch&amp;advanced=1&amp;fulltext=Testerian+catechisms\">related articles</a></span>; try the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//edwardbetts.com/find_link?q=Testerian_catechisms\">Find link tool</a> for suggestions.  <small><i>(January 2016)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:3.-_DCCCLXXIX.0001_-_Catecismo_Testeriano_o_Tasteriano_c_1524.tif\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/27/3.-_DCCCLXXIX.0001_-_Catecismo_Testeriano_o_Tasteriano_c_1524.tif/lossy-page1-300px-3.-_DCCCLXXIX.0001_-_Catecismo_Testeriano_o_Tasteriano_c_1524.tif.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"221\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/27/3.-_DCCCLXXIX.0001_-_Catecismo_Testeriano_o_Tasteriano_c_1524.tif/lossy-page1-450px-3.-_DCCCLXXIX.0001_-_Catecismo_Testeriano_o_Tasteriano_c_1524.tif.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/27/3.-_DCCCLXXIX.0001_-_Catecismo_Testeriano_o_Tasteriano_c_1524.tif/lossy-page1-600px-3.-_DCCCLXXIX.0001_-_Catecismo_Testeriano_o_Tasteriano_c_1524.tif.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2928\" data-file-height=\"2156\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:3.-_DCCCLXXIX.0001_-_Catecismo_Testeriano_o_Tasteriano_c_1524.tif\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Testerian catechism, c. 1524. <a href=\"/wiki/Center_for_the_Study_of_Mexican_History\" title=\"Center for the Study of Mexican History\">Centre of Studies of History of Mexico Carso</a></div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Testerian catechisms </b>(Spanish: <i>Catecismos testerianos</i>) are religious documents used in the evangelization of the New Spain. They explain the Catholic doctrine through images based on indigenous conventions prior to the <a href=\"/wiki/Spanish_conquest_of_the_Aztec_Empire\" title=\"Spanish conquest of the Aztec Empire\">Conquest of Mexico</a> and western Spanish writing and other <a href=\"/wiki/Mesoamerican_languages\" title=\"Mesoamerican languages\">languages</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> These documents were an attempt to be educative materials for those religious that did not know the aboriginal languages then spoken in the territory that is now Mexico. They received their name for <a href=\"/wiki/Jacobo_de_Testera\" title=\"Jacobo de Testera\">Jacobo of Testera</a>, a <a href=\"/wiki/Franciscan_friar\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Franciscan friar\">Franciscan friar</a> who elaborated catechisms of this type.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Context\">Context</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Testerian_catechisms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Context\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The missionariwes who participated in the evangelization of the new lands of the American continent looked for ways to transmit the new doctrine.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> TMesoamerican images and documents were subject to destruction, as they were considered idolatric materials, but were tolerated  when used in a religious context. Theatrical representations, music, architecture, public sermons, among others, supported the new religious precepts.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The Testerian catechisms were used to transmit the  <a href=\"/wiki/Ten_Commandments\" title=\"Ten Commandments\">Ten Commandments</a> and  prayers like the <a href=\"/wiki/Lord%27s_Prayer\" title=\"Lord&#39;s Prayer\">Lord's Prayer</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/Hail_Mary\" title=\"Hail Mary\">Hail Mary</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Testerian_catechisms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/45px-Commons-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/59px-Commons-logo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1024\" data-file-height=\"1376\" /></td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text plainlist\">Wikimedia Commons has media related to <i><b><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Testerian_catechisms\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"commons:Category:Testerian catechisms\">Testerian catechisms</a></b></i>.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"listaref\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-:0-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-:0_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-:0_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-:0_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Mor\u00edn Gonz\u00e1lez, Aid\u00e9 (2005). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.iifilologicas.unam.mx/pnovohispano/uploads/memoxviii/05_art_97.pdf\">\"Catecismo testeriano: una lectura de evangelizaci\u00f3n\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. <i>XVIII Encuentro de Investigadores del Pensamiento Novohispano</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2015-12-11</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=XVIII+Encuentro+de+Investigadores+del+Pensamiento+Novohi